{{Quote|You are far more likely to encounter a common tactic used by the Alliance called the space-snipe. In this defense, groups of fighters, usually X-wings, are placed in key hiding places around a system. Asteroid fields, gas giants, planets with large oceans or thick cloud cover all hide small fighter bases. These bases work in tandem to attack isolated ships, including supply ships jumping into the system.|[[Michael Unther]]|<ref name="A World to Conquer">{{JournalCite|2|A World to Conquer}}</ref>}}
The '''space-snipe''' strategy was a tactical doctrine that involved forces defending a [[Star system/Legends|star system]] in many instances of [[Planetary assault tactics|planetary assault]]. The strategy consisted of hiding [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] bases in [[Gas giant/Legends|gas giants]], within [[Asteroid field/Legends|asteroid fields]], on [[Planet/Legends|planets]] with large [[Ocean/Legends|oceans]], or on planets with thick cloud cover within or around the planetary system to be defended. Starfighter groups would operate in tandem from these bases, attacking isolated [[Starship/Legends|ships]] during the [[Orbit/Legends|orbit]] phase of a planetary invasion.<ref name="A World to Conquer" />

Naval strategist [[Michael Unther]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] encountered this strategy during the [[battle of Gorbah]] which cost him at least a [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]] of fighters and several starships before the enemies fled the system.<ref name="A World to Conquer" />

